      <odd id="aspace_9afc2b6e31d36190a2a23eb7b2a5bb41">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 38-B (YRG 38-B), Records documenting specific sports at Yale.</p>  
      </odd>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_e8c8fce99bf40b52905f3eacb199766f">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The materials were transferred from the Department of Athletics, 2004-2007.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_4ba7a929790615bad2b25d19582224f4">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
         <p>Original motion picture films and videotapes may not be played. Researchers should consult a reference archivist for policies and procedures governing the creation of duplicating masters and use copies of original items.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_417d5bfe62c176071ee0b5fd0ea94243">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Department of Athletics, Yale University, Motion Pictures Documenting Men's Crew (RU 968). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_4bf88ee88174df00311d20c17a4ffa9f">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The materials are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_193fe9890ba2f6db66272cbd0969b22b">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of 16 mm films and VHS videotapes documenting men's crew races and training at Yale.</p>
         <p>There is also film of the Yale-Harvard boat races, circa 1930, with film of the 1930 Yale-Army football game donated by John Kieffer (see RU 971, Accession 2013-A-082).</p>  
      </scopecontent>
